<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/70174936-jack-taylor"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1502125946i/70174936._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/70174936-jack-taylor">Jack Taylor</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Yes, this book is absolutely fine if you have only a rudimentary knowledge of Napoleon&apos;s life as informing you about that topic is the book&apos;s primary <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Yes, this book is absolutely fine if you have only a rudimentary knowledge of Napoleon's life as informing you about that topic is the book's primary aim. It starts from Napoleon's birth and details his life in an accessible (and sometimes amusing) way right through to his death. <br /><a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
