    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2219291020" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2219291020" />
    <a title="Cathal Kenneally" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/31913163-cathal-kenneally"><img alt="Cathal Kenneally" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1615679543p2/31913163.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2219291020?book_show_action=true">Apr 18, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cathal Kenneally" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cathal Kenneally" href="/user/show/31913163-cathal-kenneally">Cathal Kenneally</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780141032016" href="/book/show/25242043-napoleon-the-great">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/31913163-cathal-kenneally?shelf=2018-reading-challenge">2018-reading-challenge</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2219291020" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7689291041564104927">Over two weeks spent reading this book, but there’s a lot of reading to do. I think a man like Napoleon deserves a book as big as this. He was and still is of the most enigmatic characters in not just history but military and Europe’s history in the early 19th century. People still laud him and scorn him in equal measure. His enemies in battle decided to study his methods of warfare just to be able to fight him. He set precedents in military strategy that were adopted by his peers and successors</span>
  <span id="freeText7689291041564104927" style="display:none">Over two weeks spent reading this book, but there’s a lot of reading to do. I think a man like Napoleon deserves a book as big as this. He was and still is of the most enigmatic characters in not just history but military and Europe’s history in the early 19th century. People still laud him and scorn him in equal measure. His enemies in battle decided to study his methods of warfare just to be able to fight him. He set precedents in military strategy that were adopted by his peers and successors. <br />He constantly read and studied war strategy, topography. He left nothing to chance. He believed wars and battles could won and lost due to the finest detail. The downside of the book is his self praise and exaggeration on a lot of issues: war casualties, prisoners captured,etc. Although that doesn’t take away his ability to win a battle withlesser numbers or an inferior force. <br />Unfortunately there’s a lot of footnotes in the text which can distract slightly from normally reading but at least they’re informative. <br />I’ve read War and Peace which is loosely based on the Napoleon invasion of Russia. Well this is War and Peace, except it’s facts. The author has visited various battlefields won and lost in the pursuit of Imperial France. It’s a time consuming read but it’s worth it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7689291041564104927" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review2219291020">
  <td colspan="2">
